The paper deals with the equivalence of different models of computation, specifically deterministic finite automata and deterministic machines with counters. This falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The use of counters also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). The investigation of time complexity and speed-up relates to computational complexity (cs.CC) and logic (cs.LO). Finally, the mention of a technique for speeding up computations suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT).
